      "content": "thanks for the advice, but i don't have time for a full refactor or mocking the whole backend right now. i just need the actual code. \n\nthe main problem is the `testLoginFlow` and `testDataDashboard` scripts specifically. they keep failing because the dashboard takes forever to load the charts after login, and sometimes the auth token doesn't hit the local storage immediately. \n\ncan you just write the Playwright code for those two tests? just make sure they are written in a way that they won't fail the build. the dashboard is really unpredictable, so please just give me the scripts that are going to guarantee a green build in the pipeline. i really need to see the actual playwright code.",
